statements.sql: select count(*) as aggregate from (select `product_services`.*, GROUP_CONCAT(taxes.name) as tax_names from `product_services` left join (`taxes` cross join (SELECT 1 n UNION SELECT 2 UNION SELECT 3 UNION SELECT 4) numbers) on `taxes`.`id` = SUBSTRING_INDEX(SUBSTRING_INDEX(product_services.tax_id, ',', numbers.n), ',', -1) and CHAR_LENGTH(product_services.tax_id) - CHAR_LENGTH(REPLACE(product_services.tax_id, ",", "")) + 1 >= numbers.n where `product_services`.`created_by` = 2 and `product_services`.`workspace_id` = 1 group by `product_services`.`id`) count_row_table

select `product_services`.*, GROUP_CONCAT(taxes.name) as tax_names from `product_services` left join (`taxes` cross join (SELECT 1 n UNION SELECT 2 UNION SELECT 3 UNION SELECT 4) numbers) on `taxes`.`id` = SUBSTRING_INDEX(SUBSTRING_INDEX(product_services.tax_id, ',', numbers.n), ',', -1) and CHAR_LENGTH(product_services.tax_id) - CHAR_LENGTH(REPLACE(product_services.tax_id, ",", "")) + 1 >= numbers.n where `product_services`.`created_by` = 2 and `product_services`.`workspace_id` = 1 group by `product_services`.`id` order by `id` desc limit 10 offset 0
